Roger is an ERC Research Fellow in the School of Geography, Earth and Environmental Sciences at the University of Birmingham, and a Visiting Fellow at the University of Oxford. He received his Bachelor of Arts/Science (Hons) and PhD from Monash University in Victoria, Australia. Roger has research interests in the systematics of a diverse range of animal groups, including Mesozoic mammals, birds, and acanthomorph fishes. However, his principal research focus is on elucidating large-scale macroevolutionary and macroecological patterns, and he is currently using the Paleobiology Data Base to address key questions about the diversification of tetrapods during the Phanerozoic